<item>
            <title>[DERBY-462] DatabaseMetaData method supportsConvert() returns true</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-462</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;but we don&apos;t support the scalar escape function CONVERT yet.&lt;br/&gt;
I get the same result from both the embedded and client driver.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See JDBC 3.0 specification, appendix C.5 for a description of CONVERT and &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/api/java/sql/DatabaseMetaData.html#supportsConvert(&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/api/java/sql/DatabaseMetaData.html#supportsConvert(&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Until we do, we sould return false from supportsConvert().&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
